review_blob: On Tap.  Little head with a soft carbonation. Dark brown appearance, aroma of roasted hops and french roast coffee.  Heavier beer with smooth finish

Good, brown ale. It starts a little sweet then finishes a little sour with a metallic after taste.  Its locally brewed so I like supporting my community by drinking it.  If the pub doesnt have anything darker this beer is my go to guy.
